American rapper, Earl Simmons, popularly known as DMX, has been hospitalized following a reported drug overdose. The 50-year-old was rushed to a hospital in White Plains, New York, on Friday night after experiencing a heart attack triggered by the OD, TMZ reports. Also, his representatives while confirming the incident said that the rapper is currently hospitalized, but could not provide further details on his condition. Recall that DMX had battled substance abuse and had been to rehab several times. His last rehab stint was in 2019 after he completed a 12-month sentence for tax evasion.